  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nerigon version 2022.99.99-dev-56fcb195\r\n5.10.109-104.500.amzn2.x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux (AWS Linux)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nMy goal is to run a full mainnet archive node and run w3.eth.get_logs for any arbitrary block and return matching transactions  - I do not want or expect any pruning. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nMy problem is when via the RPC, I try and pull a transaction from approximately 90,000+ blocks back, it returns \"`ValueError: {'code': -32000, 'message': 'method handler crashed'}`\" While anything more recent than 90,000 blocks works just fine.\r\n\r\nI have subsequently tried setting prune flags to 0, but I receive a warning saying they are being ignored.\r\n\r\n`sudo ~/erigon/build/bin/erigon --datadir /mnt/opt1/mainnet --ws --http --prune.h.before 10000000 --prune.r.before 10000000 --prune.c.before 10000000 --prune.t.before 10000000\r\n\r\n`EROR[05-24|17:35:24.919] Erigon startup                           err=\"not allowed change of --prune flag, last time you used: \"`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nI have synced mainnet to what I understand is a full archive node with `\"~/erigon/build/bin/erigon --datadir /myDataDir\"`, with no additional parameters as your docs specifically state \"**Pruning: Disabled by default.\"**\r\n\r\nI then run a simple w3 call from Web3.py along the lines of:\r\n\r\nw3.eth.get_logs(\r\n            {\r\n                \"fromBlock\": 13755911,\r\n                \"toBlock\": 13755911 + 1000,\r\n                \"address\": '0xB4e16d0168e52d35CaCD2c6185b44281Ec28C9Dc',\r\n                \"topics\": '0xd78ad95fa46c994b6551d0da85fc275fe613ce37657fb8d5e3d130840159d822',\r\n            }\r\n        )\r\n\r\nwhich results in the below back trace, setting \"fromBlock\" to something near the top of the block height results in a normal RPC response with the expected data.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n````\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"mvp.py\", line 64, in findTargetTX\r\n    txn = w3.eth.get_transaction(txnHash)\r\n  File \"/mnt/opt1/anaconda3/envs/xyz/lib/python3.7/site-packages/web3/eth.py\", line 737, in get_transaction\r\n    return self._get_transaction(transaction_hash)\r\n  File \"/mnt/opt1/anaconda3/envs/xyz/lib/python3.7/site-packages/web3/module.py\", line 60, in caller\r\n    null_result_formatters)\r\n  File \"/mnt/opt1/anaconda3/envs/xyz/lib/python3.7/site-packages/web3/manager.py\", line 201, in request_blocking\r\n    null_result_formatters)\r\n  File \"/mnt/opt1/anaconda3/envs/xyz/lib/python3.7/site-packages/web3/manager.py\", line 171, in formatted_response\r\n    raise ValueError(response[\"error\"])\r\nValueError: {'code': -32000, 'message': 'method handler crashed'}\r\n````\r\n\r\n\r\nHave I synced the node correctly? It took ~5days with IOPs SSD's on AWS and the datadir is currently >1.6tb's\r\n\r\nAny assistance debugging this (without a full new sync) would be appreciated.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n",
